{
  "text": "The purpose of our study is the elucidation of GTS-21 O 4-demethylase activity as the main cause of variable pharmacokinetics of GTS-21 in dogs. To estimate the contribution of the metabolism to total clearance, we subjected Michaelis-Menten kinetic parameters of four dogs to a scaling procedure. [CITATION_1] A comparison of the in vivo pharmacokinetic parameters with the in vitro kinetic parameters revealed that the individual variability in plasma concentration was predominantly caused by GTS-21 O 4-demethylase activity. Next, we speci\u02c6ed the cytochrome P450 (CYP) enzymes that are involved with the metabolism by chemical inhibition, and quanti\u02c6ed the contents of key enzymes by enzyme-linked immunosorbent assays (ELISA).",
